trend_summary: Area shifts from mostly rural mosaic to a suburban landscape. Housing subdivisions expand steadily, roads densify, and farmland patches shrink, especially east-central. Forest cover thins near new estates, though some pockets replant. A few reservoirs and commercial nodes appear after mid-period.
notable_changes: Progressive spread of low-rise housing tracts across central and eastern sectors.
New or widened highway corridors create denser transport grid by final image.
Marked reduction of open farmland, replaced by residential development.
Emergence of small reservoirs/ponds and associated recreation areas.
Incremental loss of contiguous forest blocks, particularly along new road edges.
